.Dd Mai 22, 2001
.Dt rezept 1
.Os Koch-Suite
.Sh NAME
.Nm rezept
.Nd Recipe query and export in different formats.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm 
.Op Fl h
.Op Fl text | Fl mm Op Fl relaxed | Fl latex
.Op Fl f Ar filename Op Fl 1
.Op Fl t | Fl c | Fl i
.Ar pattern
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
requests recipes from the database and formats them in the specified
format.
If no
.Ar pattern
is specified, 
print usage and exit.
By default search for
.Ar pattern
in the
.Em menu-titles .
.Pp
.Ar pattern 
may be a combination of several searchstrings, connected by
.Dq AND .
I. e. a valid pattern is 
.Dq Muffins AND Choc . 
While the searchstrings are case-insensitive, the 
.Dq AND
has to be upper case.
.Pp
Optional paramters are:
.Bl -tag -width "TOLONG"
.It Fl f Ar filename Op Fl 1
Output goes there. By default every recipe is written into a single file
.Ar filename ,
suffixed by a 2-digit counter.
.Fl 1
makes
.Nm
write all recipes into one file
.Ar filename .
Default output location is
.Em STDOUT .
.It Fl h
Print usage and exit.
.It Fl latex
write output as latex-source
.It Fl mm Op Fl relaxed
write output in Meal-Master format.
Using
.Fl relaxed
violates the strict definitions of the Meal-Master format slightly.
Don't use it.
.It Fl text
write output as human readable text. 
This is the default.
.It Fl t
Search for 
.Ar pattern
in the menu-titles.
.It Fl c
Search for
.Ar pattern
in the categories-list.
.It Fl i
Search for
.Ar pattern
in the ingredient-lists.
.El
.\" .Sh RETURN VALUES
.\" This next request is for sections 1, 6, 7 & 8 only
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
The following environment variables affect the execution of
.Nm rezept :
.Bl -tag -width "TOLONG"
.It Ev LC_MESSAGES
.It Ev LANG
If the recipe-format allows localization of the output,
the values of these environment variables are honored.
If
.Ev LC_MESSAGES 
is set, and the defined language exists use that,
otherwise try
.Ev LANG .
If that fails to, use the default language.
